Alembic migration environment for Knowledge-OS.

## Rules

- Alembic is the only way to change the production schema. Do not alter tables manually.
- Every generated migration must be reviewed before applying. Autogenerate can miss things (e.g. enum changes, index renames).
- Use the direct session connection (`postgresql+psycopg://`), not the transaction pooler URL.
- Run from the `backend/` directory, not the repo root.

## Common commands

```bash
# Apply all pending migrations
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Create a new migration from model changes
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

# Show current revision
uv run alembic current

# Show migration history
uv run alembic history --verbose

# Roll back one step
uv run alembic downgrade -1
```

