| `529159d4d546` | Add content_artifacts table                                   |

## Notes on enum changes

Adding values to a PostgreSQL enum (`ALTER TYPE ... ADD VALUE`) cannot be rolled back once committed. Document this in the migration docstring when it applies. Removing an enum value is not possible in PostgreSQL without recreating the type.
